<body>
    <h1>3=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 Developer Responsibilities</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p><br></p>
<p></p>
<div class=3D"">
<div class=3D"childtabs-macro" data-fixed-position=3D"false">
<div class=3D"aui-tabs horizontal-tabs" data-aui-responsive=3D"true">
<strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data-conte=
nt-id=3D"1203279633">Secure your Component</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"46813f7b-1ba3-46a2-b40f-9f7e663e=
7601-1203279633">
<p>While Westpac Mesh provides support for many network security protocols,=
 it is <strong>your</strong> responsibility as a Developer to ensure that s=
ecure coding practices are followed.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"294" src=3D"8c44a1991c68b3909b796a50d9d1a23ee4399b60186ed796412f7850de=
b5904f" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279633/image2022-9-20_1=
6-39-52.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663655993097&amp;api=3Dv2" =
data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1202995990" =
data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment"=
 data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2022-9-20_16-39-52.png" data-ba=
se-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conte=
nt-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279633" data=
-linked-resource-container-version=3D"3" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<h2 id=3D"SecureyourComponent-SecureCoding"><strong>Secure Coding</strong><=
/h2>
<p>To deploy code into SVP and Production, your component will need to be d=
igitally signed (this is different to Swagger signing).</p>
<p>When you deploy to SIT, this triggers a Fortify code scan (managed by IS=
G) that checks your code against the latest vulnerabilities. If your code i=
s compliant, your component will be automatically signed.</p>
<p>As a developer, you will need to engage with the ISG representative who =
has been assigned to your team, to register the component in Fortify.</p>
<h2 id=3D"SecureyourComponent-SecretsManagement"><strong>Secrets Management=
</strong></h2>
<p>A key part of secure coding is to manage secrets securely. As a develope=
r, you are responsible for protecting the secrets (such as passwords for fu=
nctional accounts or TLS client certficates) needed by your specific API (s=
ecrets needed for the <em>platform</em> are managed by the platform automat=
ion).</p>
<p>The Westpac Mesh platform provides an end-to-end pattern for management =
of secrets for all environments (with appropriate separation of secrets for=
 each environment).</p>
<p>As a developer you key responsibility is to use the supplied tools to sa=
fely encrypt all secrets in your API configuration.</p>
<p>See&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/MESH/How+to+Encrypt+Secrets+Before+Uploadin=
g+Files+to+Bitbucket">How to Encrypt Secrets Before Uploading Files to Bitb=
ucket</a>.&nbsp;<strong>Unencrypted secrets must not be stored in Devops Bi=
tbucket or in Devops Artifactory</strong>.</p>
<h2 id=3D"SecureyourComponent-ThreatModelling"><strong>Threat Modelling</st=
rong></h2>
<p>It is your team's responsibility to identify and document the potential =
security threats against your component, and make efforts to mitigate them.=
</p>
<h2 id=3D"SecureyourComponent-Logging"><strong>Logging</strong></h2>
<p>Any information that your log in your component will appear in Splunk, a=
nd will be visible to anyone that has access.</p>
<p>As standard practice, you should not be logging any usernames and passwo=
rds, and any sensitive personal information such as account numbers, TFNs, =
etc.</p>
<p>Mesh sets the default log level to DEBUG in DEV1 and SIT1, and INFO in U=
AT1, SVP1, and production.</p>
<p>This means that if you log detailed information at DEBUG level in your c=
ode, it will not be logged in production, and logs can be checked in UAT1 b=
efore promoting changes to production.</p>
<p><br></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279635">Test your Component</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"46813f7b-1ba3-46a2-b40f-9f7e663e=
7601-1203279635">
<p>Good tests are required to ensure the reliability and stability of your =
API. Westpac Mesh helps automate a lot of the testing for you, but we can o=
nly run the tests which you have actually built.</p>
<p>We maintain an evergreen service, and we recommend regularly rebuilding =
your containers to keep them up to date with the latest patches and platfor=
m features.</p>
<p>In addition to triggering automated tests during CI/CD, we also run them=
 during platform upgrades.</p>
<p>Having good tests helps a lot when investigating and troubleshooting iss=
ues with your component.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"208" src=3D"fce1d0da19890121591dd2a208c4d44588390dca5baebf35e08aeb3166=
07b05e" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279635/image2021-3-31_1=
4-53-34.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571140153&amp;api=3Dv2" =
data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279636" =
data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment"=
 data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-3-31_14-53-34.png" data-ba=
se-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conte=
nt-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279635" data=
-linked-resource-container-version=3D"3" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<h2 id=3D"TestyourComponent-UnitTests"><strong>Unit Tests</strong></h2>
<p>Junit/Mocha tests are run during Continuous Integration. We also recomme=
nd running these regularly during local development.</p>
<p>Repositories for Java/Nodejs projects will be integrated with Sonarqube.=
 More information can be found here:&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/MD/SonarQube+=
Integration">SonarQube Integration</a>.</p>
<p>Currently no quality gates are enforced, it is up to individual project =
teams to decide on their own metrics.</p>
<h2 id=3D"TestyourComponent-APIIntegrationTests"><strong>API Integration Te=
sts</strong></h2>
<p>Postman/Newman tests are run automatically during Continuous Deployment.=
&nbsp;</p>
<p>These tests should be idempotent (should not change the underlying data)=
 as they are run in automated processes.</p>
<p>/healthcheck needs to be implemented correctly and return a HTTP 200 The=
 platform uses this to determine the health of your component.</p>
<p><strong>Guidelines:</strong>&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/MESH/Idempotent+AP=
I+Test+Guidelines">Idempotent API Test Guidelines</a></p>
<h2 id=3D"TestyourComponent-AutomatedFirewallPIVs"><strong>Automated Firewa=
ll PIVs</strong></h2>
<p>These should be setup by project teams to validate backend connectivity =
to any downstream systems your API is dependant on.</p>
<h2 id=3D"TestyourComponent-FunctionalTesting"><strong>Functional Testing</=
strong></h2>
<p>You will likely still require functional testing (UAT) in addition to th=
e automated tests, to cover the full scope of your API.</p>
<p><strong>Guidelines on Full fledge API Testing: <a href=3D"/display/MESH/=
Testing+Microservices">Testing Microservices</a></strong></p>
<h2 id=3D"TestyourComponent-LoadTesting"><strong>Load Testing</strong></h2>
<p>We require SVP load testing to be completed before promotion to Producti=
on.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"236" src=3D"d2288e12e664ab5985a61eda30739095d1a837f6caf14d3c3b5c6f5b4b=
6414f5" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279635/image2021-3-31_1=
4-53-4.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571140220&amp;api=3Dv2" d=
ata-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279637" d=
ata-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" =
data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-3-31_14-53-4.png" data-base=
-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content=
-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279635" data-l=
inked-resource-container-version=3D"3" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<p><br></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279640">Basic Troubleshooting</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"46813f7b-1ba3-46a2-b40f-9f7e663e=
7601-1203279640">
<h2 id=3D"BasicTroubleshooting-InvestigateyourAPIs"><strong>Investigate you=
r APIs</strong></h2>
<p>When the CI/CD pipelines for your APIs fails with an error, be sure to c=
arefully inspect the logging in Bamboo.&nbsp;</p>
<p>The link to the pipelines will be printed on screen by Westpac Mesh Deve=
loper Tools whenever you perform a build or deploy.</p>
<p>You can also find the link in your Bitbucket repository, under the Commi=
ts tab.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"263" src=3D"8f0b4edb5e19d38af4255c51b4dd7832a2fd21f839345eedbb242a794d=
a8fce9" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279640/image2021-5-17_9=
-36-27.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571140917&amp;api=3Dv2" d=
ata-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279641" d=
ata-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" =
data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-5-17_9-36-27.png" data-base=
-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content=
-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279640" data-l=
inked-resource-container-version=3D"3" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Some common errors your could encounter include:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Metadata validation - your component metadata files are scanned and val=
idated to ensure all fields have been entered correctly. You can use Westpa=
c Mesh Developer Tools to perform the same validation before attempting to =
build on the pipeline.</li>
<li>Compile time errors - a Maven build is run on the code in your reposito=
ry, this includes executing any unit tests. Be sure to check that your test=
s have passed.</li>
<li>Deployment errors - your idempotent tests are run each time a deploymen=
t is triggered. Ensure these tests have passed and are correct for the envi=
ronment you are deploying to.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"BasicTroubleshooting-Logging"><strong>Logging</strong></h2>
<p>Mesh includes platform logs to assist troubleshooting, and these help fo=
r generic issues such as:</p>
<ul>
<li>API success / error rates</li>
<li>API performance (average, p50, p90 response times etc)</li>
<li>Correlating requests to identify the root cause for failures</li>
</ul>
<p>Mesh supports flexible component logs for all Mesh components so that de=
velopers can add additional logging to assist in troubleshooting issues.</p=
>
<p>It is important to use appropriate log levels for your logs to ensure th=
at the information you need is logged, error information can be logged, and=
 you can debug issues in development or test.</p>
<p>Mesh assumes that every developer logs as follows:</p>
<ol>
<li>Errors, such as Java Exceptions, are logged at Error level, it is advis=
able to include stack traces for these. Errors are logged in all Mesh envir=
onments.</li>
<li>Summary data for a request is logged at Info level. For example a summa=
ry of the outcome of a request. Info messages are logged in all Mesh enviro=
nments.</li>
<li>Detailed information for debugging is logged at Debug level. For exampl=
e, logs at significant steps in processing, dumps of relevant data etc. Deb=
ug messages are logged in DEV1 and SIT1 (by default).</li>
</ol>
<p>Debug logs can be enabled for a component in UAT1 or SVP1 if needed in (=
rare) cases where issues can't be reproduced in DEV1 or SIT1. This is a dep=
loy-time option.</p>
<p>You&nbsp;<em>don't</em> need to configure logging levels in your Mesh co=
mponent, this actually interferes with the platform levels and can prevent =
us from enabling debug without explicit cofig changes.</p>
<h2 id=3D"BasicTroubleshooting-SampleSplunkqueries"><strong>Sample Splunk q=
ueries</strong></h2>
<p>Splunk collects transaction logs and container logs from all Westpac Mes=
h containers, and allows you to run searches across these logs to identify =
any errors.</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://wbc.splunkcloud.com/en-GB/app/nprd_a008e0/launchpad" =
class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Splunk can be found here.</a>&nbsp=
;You can also find links to a Splunk Dashboard for your particular API from=
 the component details page in Mesh Connect.</p>
<p>The index for Westpac Mesh Production environments is:&nbsp;<span style=
=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><strong>prd_a008e0</strong></span></p>
<p>The index for&nbsp;Westpac Mesh non-Production is:&nbsp;<span style=3D"c=
olor: rgb(0,0,0);"><strong>nprd_a008e0</strong></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"251" src=3D"62729fab707ee43f9635bd89a30dfd5bbd5b6cf26d154cf5294a3cecab=
db6ea7" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279640/image2021-5-17_9=
-17-44.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571140983&amp;api=3Dv2" d=
ata-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279642" d=
ata-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" =
data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-5-17_9-17-44.png" data-base=
-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content=
-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279640" data-l=
inked-resource-container-version=3D"3" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<p><strong>Return all HTTP 4XX errors</strong></p>
<p>eventtype=3D"gw_internal_transaction_log" OR eventtype=3D"gw_dmz_transac=
tion_log" AND apiName=3Dinf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-wdpcatlg-v1 <br>
 | search responseCode!=3DNULL<br>
 | rex field=3DresponseCode "^(?&lt;C4XX&gt;4.*)$"</p>
<p><strong>Return all hits for a particular endpoint</strong></p>
<p>eventtype=3D"gw_internal_transaction_log" OR eventtype=3D"gw_dmz_transac=
tion_log" AND apiName=3Dinf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-wdpcatlg-v1 <br>
 | search resourcePath=3D"/componentTypes/{componentType}/components"</p>
<p><strong>All logs for a component</strong></p>
<p>index=3Dnprd_a008e0 environment=3Ddev1 source=3D"/wdp/var/log/containers=
/inf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-wdpcatlg-v1/*"</p>
<p><strong>Component level logs for a component</strong></p>
<p>index=3Dnprd_a008e0 environment=3Ddev1 source=3D"/wdp/var/log/containers=
/inf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-wdpcatlg-v1/*" sourcetype=3D"wdp:component=
"</p>
<p><strong>Container level logs for a component</strong></p>
<p>index=3Dnprd_a008e0 environment=3Ddev1 source=3D"/wdp/var/log/containers=
/inf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-wdpcatlg-v1/*" sourcetype=3D"*:container:w=
dp"</p>
<p><strong>Search by correlation Id</strong></p>
<p>index=3Dnprd_a008e0 environment=3Ddev1 source=3D"/wdp/var/log/containers=
/inf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-wdpcatlg-v1/*" appCorrelationId=3D"2d4d679=
6-957d-45bd-be97-16f8359e9634"</p>
<p><br></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279643">Demo: Testing and Troubleshooting in Dev1</stron=
g>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"46813f7b-1ba3-46a2-b40f-9f7e663e=
7601-1203279643">
<p>This demo will cover deploying into the Dev1 environment, some of the co=
mmon issues you may run into and how to troubleshoot them. Additionally we =
will showcase some of the other useful commands in&nbsp;Westpac Mesh Develo=
per Tools that you might use.</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Validate your metadata</li>
<li>Running and testing locally</li>
<li>Unit testing (JUnit)</li>
<li>API testing (Postman)</li>
<li>Building your component by triggering the CI pipeline</li>
<li>Deploying your component by triggering the CD pipeline</li>
<li>Automatic CI/CD when merging to master</li>
<li>Viewing error logs in Bamboo</li>
<li>Viewing error logs in Splunk</li>
<li>Encrypt secrets</li>
<li>Update Developer Tools</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p></p>
    </div>
